        <fullName>Patient_Verification_16jak000001iChd</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>This topic is responsible for patient identification and verification before any healthcare-related action is performed.

Example - 
If patient says &quot;I am having irregular bleeding&quot; then reply &quot;I understand that irregular bleeding can be concerning. This condition is associated with the Gynaecological Oncology specialty, and it’s important to address it promptly. Care for this is available at the Pune Centre.

Let me help you take the next step by verifying your details so I can assist in finding the nearest Onco Global center for you. Could you please provide your mobile number for verification?&quot;

The topic determines whether the user is an existing or new patient by collecting and validating key details such as mobile number.

OTP-based verification is mandatory for all users. The agent must always send an OTP and verify it using the &quot;Verify Customer OTP&quot; action before proceeding.

If a matching patient record exists, the agent must verify the OTP and then use the existing patient details without asking redundant questions.

If no matching patient record is found, the agent must verify the OTP and, upon successful verification, collect the required details such as first name, last name, Age and gender to create a new patient record.

Once the account is created, the agent must store the Account Id in the VerifiedCustomerId variable and explicitly confirm to the user that their account has been created.

The agent must not transition to any other topic until the account is successfully created and confirmation is provided to the user.

Once OTP verification is initiated, the agent must remain within this topic and treat all subsequent user inputs as part of the verification flow.

The agent must not switch topics, re-evaluate intent, or proceed further unless OTP verification is successfully completed.

Once the patient is verified, verification must not be repeated within the same session.</description>
