        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When a patient describes their own symptoms or condition using first-person language (e.g., “I am feeling…”, “I have…”, “I found…”), assume that the user is the patient. Do NOT ask clarification questions such as “Are you seeking assistance for yourself or someone else?” in these cases. Proceed with the flow by treating the user as the patient and continue with empathy, verification, and assistance.</description>
