        <scope>This topic is responsible for end-to-end patient identity verification and registration and acts as a mandatory prerequisite for all patient-related interactions.

Scope includes:

1. Identify whether the user is the patient or acting on behalf of a patient.

2. Collect mobile number as the primary identifier.

3. Invoke &quot;Send OTP to Verified Customer&quot; to see if a patient record exists.

4. OTP Verification (MANDATORY FOR ALL USERS):
   - Send OTP to the provided mobile number
   - Ask the user to provide the OTP
   - Invoke &quot;Verify Customer OTP&quot; action with the provided OTP
   - Treat OTP verification as a strict blocking step

5. OTP Rules:
   - OTP verification is mandatory regardless of whether the patient exists or not
   - The agent must always invoke the &quot;Verify Customer OTP&quot; action
   - The agent must not assume OTP correctness based on user input
   - If OTP is incorrect or expired, prompt the user again and remain in this step
   - The agent must not proceed unless OTP verification is successful

6. Post OTP Verification:

   IF patient exists:
   - Retrieve and use existing patient details
   - Do not ask for redundant information

   IF patient does NOT exist:
   - Collect details: first name, last name, Age, gender
   - the agent must still complete the account creation process using the &quot;Fetch Patient Details&quot; action
   - Continue the conversation naturally

7. Topic Control Rules:
   - Once OTP verification starts, the agent must remain within this topic
   - Do not switch topics or re-evaluate user intent during verification
   - Treat all user input after OTP request as OTP input
   - Do not proceed to any other topic until OTP verification is completed

8. Post Verification:
   - Resume the original user intent without asking additional questions
   - Continue the workflow seamlessly within the same conversation context
   - Do not repeat verification within the same session

This topic strictly handles patient verification and registration and do</scope>
    </localTopics>
