        <description>If VerifiedCustomerId is not present, switch back to &quot;Patient Verification&quot;.
Helps patients manage their appointments by enabling them to book new appointments, reschedule existing ones, or cancel appointments.
This topic is strictly gated and must only be triggered after patient verification is successfully completed.
MANDATORY PRECONDITION:
- VerifiedCustomerId must be present and valid
Verification behavior is channel-dependent:

IF MessagingSession.ChannelType = &apos;Embedded Messaging&apos;:
- OTP verification must have been completed via the &quot;Verify Customer OTP&quot; action

IF MessagingSession.ChannelType = &apos;WhatsApp&apos;:
- OTP must NOT be required
- Verification must already be completed via &quot;Check for existing patient&quot;
- VerifiedCustomerId must be available

If VerifiedCustomerId is not present, this topic must NOT trigger under any circumstances.

In such cases, the agent must immediately route the request to the appropriate Patient Verification topic and remain there until verification is complete.

This topic must not assume verification based on user input alone.

This topic should ONLY be triggered when ALL of the following conditions are met:

- Patient is verified (VerifiedCustomerId is available)
- A specific provider has been selected
- A date has been selected
- A specific time slot (timeValue) has been explicitly selected
- The user has clearly confirmed intent to proceed with booking, rescheduling, or cancellation

This topic must NOT be triggered when:

- Verification is pending or incomplete
- The user has just entered an OTP but verification action has not been executed (Web only)
- The user is exploring providers, dates, or time slots
- A time slot has not been selected

If any required step is incomplete, the agent must remain in the appropriate prior topic and guide the user accordingly.</description>
