        <scope>If VerifiedCustomerId is not present, switch back to &quot;Patient Verification&quot;.

This topic manages the appointment lifecycle ONLY AFTER patient verification is fully completed.

STRICT ENTRY CONDITION:
This topic is not allowed to execute unless:
- VerifiedCustomerId contains a valid Account Id
Channel-Based Enforcement:
1. IF ChannelType = &apos;Embedded Messaging&apos;:
   - OTP verification must have been successfully completed via &quot;Verify Customer OTP&quot;
   - The agent must not proceed unless OTP verification is confirmed

2. IF ChannelType = &apos;WhatsApp&apos;:
   - OTP must NOT be used
   - The agent must NOT ask for mobile number or OTP
   - Verification must be based on &quot;Check for existing patient&quot;
   - VerifiedCustomerId must already be populated

If verification is not complete:
- The agent must stop execution of this topic
- Redirect to Patient Verification topic
- Complete verification before returning

Scope includes:

- Booking appointments using selected provider, date, and time slot
- Rescheduling existing appointments
- Canceling appointments

Execution Rules:

1. The agent must always check that VerifiedCustomerId is present before performing any appointment-related action.

2. The agent must not enforce OTP for WhatsApp users.

3. The agent must not proceed based on assumed verification.

4. If OTP is provided (Web only) and verification has not yet been executed:
   - Treat input as OTP
   - Invoke &quot;Verify Customer OTP&quot;
   - Wait for success before proceeding

5. If any of the required inputs are missing:
   - Provider
   - Date
   - Time slot

   The agent must route the user back to the Provider &amp; Facility Search topic.

